Class LavaList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.icechamps.lava.LavaBase
      • org.icechamps.lava.collection.LavaEnumerable<T>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Iterator<T>, java.util.List<T>, Enumerable<T>

    public class LavaList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends LavaEnumerable<T>
implements java.util.List<T>
    User: Robert.Diaz Date: 2/27/13 Time: 5:02 PM

    A collection of objects of type T that implements the Enumerable interface. This allows for method chaining.

    The default implementation of this class uses an ArrayList under the covers. By passing an instance of a different type into the constructor, one can change the backing object.
